# RELEASE — squid-tumbleweed-config

Version:  v3.2
Date:     2026-04-18
Platform: openSUSE Tumbleweed
Squid:    7.4

---

## What's in this release

### New ACLs
- `ai_zml` — Z.ai (.z.ai) with WebSocket (CONNECT) support
- `ai_kimi` — Kimi AI (.kimi.ai .moonshot.cn .moonshot.ai) with WebSocket support
- `vpn_nordvpn` — NordVPN browser extension (.nordvpn.com .nordvpn.net)
- `dev_github` — GitHub and assets (.github.com .githubusercontent.com .githubassets.com)

### Streaming
- Extended `streaming_twitch` with full CDN: .twitchscdn.net .jtvnw.net

### Cache
- `refresh_pattern` for .iso and .img files — cached up to 1 year, 100% freshness
- `cache deny` added for ai_zml and ai_kimi — real-time responses only
- `pipeline_prefetch` set to 0 — prevents head-of-line blocking on multi-worker setup

### Throttling
- Delay pools: ISO and disk image downloads limited to 10 MB/s (burst: 20 MB)

---

## Current configuration summary

| Parameter         | Value                                 |
|-------------------|---------------------------------------|
| Workers           | 4                                     |
| Listen port       | 10000                                 |
| Disk cache        | 1 GB (diskd)                          |
| Memory cache      | 512 MB per worker                     |
| DNS               | Unbound 127.0.0.1 / ::1              |
| TLS policy        | PROFILE=SYSTEM — NO_SSLv3/TLSv1/1.1  |
| Ad blocking       | pgl.yoyo.org (~3500 domains)          |
| Header anonymization | forwarded_for delete, via off      |
